{{Campaignbox Bahraini uprising}} '''Bahiya Al Aradi ''' ({{lang-ar| بهیة العرادی }}) (? &ndash; 16 March 2011) was the first woman killed<ref> {{cite news | author= | title = Bahraini woman dies of gunshot wound - opposition | date= 22 March 2011| publisher= [[REUTERS]] | url = https://af.reuters.com/article/worldNews/idAFTRE72E24K20110322?pageNumber=1&virtualBrandChannel=0| accessdate=}}</ref> in the [[Bahraini uprising (2011–present)|Bahraini Uprising]]. She is notable as the first female victim in the [[Bahraini uprising (2011–present)|Bahraini Uprising]]. She has been called a [[shahid|shaheeda]], or female martyr, by her family.<ref>{{cite news | author= | title = Family mourns senseless death of Bahiya Al Aradi, in wrong part of Bahrain at wrong time
| date= 23 March 2011| publisher= The National World | url = http://www.thenational.ae/news/world/middle-east/family-mourns-senseless-death-of-bahiya-al-aradi-in-wrong-part-of-bahrain-at-wrong-time| accessdate=}}</ref>
On March 16, the government allowed her brother to visit her for a few minutes in Bahrain Defense Force Hospital ([[Bahrain Royal Medical Services]]).<ref>{{cite news | author= | title = Bahrain: Investigate Deaths Linked to Crackdown | date= 29 March 2011| publisher= Human Rights Watch | url = https://www.hrw.org/news/2011/03/29/bahrain-investigate-deaths-linked-crackdown| accessdate=}} </ref>
She died on hospital from injuries she received when she was hit in the back by [[Shotgun shell#Birdshot|birdshot]] pellets fired from a range of 50 to 75 meters.<ref> {{cite news | author= | title = Women in Bahrain on International Day to end violence against women: constantly subjected to torture, arrests and violence | date= 25 November 2011| publisher= Bahrain Center for Human Rights | url = http://www.bahrainrights.org/en/node/4861| accessdate=}}</ref> On March 20, the hospital announced that she had died of her injuries. At least one bullet had entered al-Aradi's head from behind. There was no exit wound.
==Personal life== Al Aradi was never married.<ref> {{cite news | author= | title = Family mourns senseless death of Bahiya Al Aradi, in wrong part of Bahrain at wrong time | date= 23 March 2011| publisher= The National World | url = http://www.thenational.ae/news/world/middle-east/family-mourns-senseless-death-of-bahiya-al-aradi-in-wrong-part-of-bahrain-at-wrong-time| accessdate=}}</ref>
