{{Infobox baseball biography | name= Marian Bryson | image= | image_size= | team= {{small|[[All-American Girls Professional Baseball League]]}} | position= [[Pitcher]] <!-- MISSING DATA - If you or someone you know has information regarding this player, please contact User:MusiCitizen – | birth_date= {{Birth date and age|YY|MM|DD}} | birth_place= | death_date= {{Death date and age|YY|MM|DD|YY|MM|DD}} | death_place= --> | bats= Right | throws= Right | teams= *[[Peoria Redwings]] (1946) |highlights= *Women in Baseball – AAGPBL Permanent Display at Baseball Hall of Fame and Museum (since 1988) }}
'''Marion Bryson''' was a right handed [[pitcher]] in the [[All-American Girls Professional Baseball League]] who played for the [[Peoria Redwings]] in its 1946 season. Bryson was born in [[Los Angeles]], [[California]]. She was dubbed ''Scotty''.<ref name=AAGPBL>[http://www.aagpbl.org/index.cfm/profiles/bryson-marian/875 All-American Girls Professional Baseball League Official Website]</ref>
Bryson posted a 0-8 record with a 5.32 [[earned run average|ERA]] in 14 pitching appearances, [[strikeout|striking out]] 11 batters while [[base on balls|walking]] 36 in 71.0 [[innings pitched|innings of work]]. As a hitter, she went 2-for-18 for a .112 [[batting average]].<ref name=AAGPBL/>
Bryson is part of the AAGPBL permanent display at the [[Baseball Hall of Fame and Museum]] at [[Cooperstown, New York]] opened in 1988, which is dedicated to the entire league rather than any individual figure.<ref>[http://baseballhall.org/discover/league-of-women-ballplayers Baseball Hall of Fame and Museum Official Website]</ref>
